            {
              "rowId": 11,
              "keyParts": [
                11,
                "p1",
                "verse",
                "v2",
                "content"
              ],
              "value": "‘Appoint the cities of refuge, of which I spoke to you through Moses,"
            },
            {
              "rowId": 12,
              "keyParts": [
                "v002_ESV_JOS_020",
                12,
                "p1",
                "verse",
                "v2",
                "plain_text"
              ],
              "value": "2 “Say to the people of Israel, ‘Appoint the cities of refuge, of which I spoke to you through Moses,"
            },
            {
              "rowId": 13,
              "keyParts": [
                13,
                "p1",
                "verse",
                "v3",
                "label"
              ],
              "value": "3"
            },
            {
              "rowId": 14,
              "keyParts": [
                14,
                "p1",
                "verse",
                "v3",
                "content"
              ],
              "value": "that the manslayer who strikes any person without intent or unknowingly may flee there. They shall be for you a refuge from the avenger of blood."
            },
            {
              "rowId": 15,
              "keyParts": [
                "v003_ESV_JOS_020",
                15,
                "p1",
                "verse",
                "v3",
                "plain_text"
              ],
              "value": "3 that the manslayer who strikes any person without intent or unknowingly may flee there. They shall be for you a refuge from the avenger of blood."
            },
            {
              "rowId": 16,
              "keyParts": [
                16,
                "p1",
                "verse",
                "v4",
                "label"
              ],
              "value": "4"
            },
            {
              "rowId": 17,
              "keyParts": [
                17,
                "p1",
                "verse",
                "v4",
                "content"
              ],
              "value": "He shall flee to one of these cities and shall stand"
            },
            {
              "rowId": 18,
              "keyParts": [
                18,
                "p1",
                "verse",
                "v4",
                "note",
                "x"
              ],
              "value": "#[Deut. 21:19;Ruth 4:1,2;Ps. 127:5]"
            },
            {
              "rowId": 19,
              "keyParts": [
                19,
                "p1",
                "verse",
                "v4",
                "content"
              ],
              "value": "at the entrance of the gate of the city and explain his case to the elders of that city. Then they shall take him into the city and give him a place, and he shall remain with them."
            },
            {
              "rowId": 20,
              "keyParts": [
                "v004_ESV_JOS_020",
                20,
                "p1",
                "verse",
                "v4",
                "plain_text"
              ],
              "value": "4 He shall flee to one of these cities and shall stand at the entrance of the gate of the city and explain his case to the elders of that city. Then they shall take him into the city and give him a place, and he shall remain with them."
            },
            {
              "rowId": 21,
              "keyParts": [
                21,
                "p1",
                "verse",
                "v5",
                "label"
              ],
              "value": "5"
            },
            {
              "rowId": 22,
              "keyParts": [
                22,
                "p1",
                "verse",
                "v5",
                "content"
              ],
              "value": "And if the avenger of blood pursues him, they shall not give up the manslayer into his hand, because he struck his neighbor unknowingly, and did not hate him in the past."
            },
            {
              "rowId": 23,
              "keyParts": [
                "v005_ESV_JOS_020",
                23,
                "p1",
                "verse",
                "v5",
                "plain_text"
              ],
              "value": "5 And if the avenger of blood pursues him, they shall not give up the manslayer into his hand, because he struck his neighbor unknowingly, and did not hate him in the past."
            },
            {
              "rowId": 24,
              "keyParts": [
                24,
                "p1",
                "verse",
                "v6",
                "label"
              ],
              "value": "6"
            },
